In 2021, they will construct Ontario's first mass-timber, low-carbon institutional building named The Arbour. The modern, sustainable design by Moriyama & Teshima Architects and Acton Ostry Architects has already received awards: the Sustainability Prize at the 2019 MIPIM/Architectural Review Future Project Awards, and the First Award in the Institutional Concept category at Rethinking the Future's 2018 Architecture.
